title: Birds are taking over the skies right now. Here's what you can see in New England during fall migration
dc:creator: WBUR
description: According to BirdCast, a migration tracker through The Cornell Lab, roughly 1,000 birds crossed over Suffolk County on Tuesday night as part of this fall's yearly migration.
